WEBVTT

00:00:00.820 --> 00:00:10.680
Alif Lam Meem, Allah, La ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hibb Al-Qayyum,

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:18.200
Nazala alayka Al-Kitab Bil-Haqq Musabdiqa Lima Bayna Yadihi Wa Anzala Al-Tawrat Wa Al-Injeel,

00:00:18.200 --> 00:00:22.280
Min Qabnu Hudan Li Al-Nas Wa Anzala Al-Furqan,

00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:27.560
Inna Allatheena Kafuroo Bi Ayat Allahi Lahum Azaabuhu Shadeed,

00:00:27.560 --> 00:00:31.440
Wa Allahu Azizun Zuntiqan,

00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:36.540
Inna Allaha La Yahta Aleyhi Shajajin Fi Al-Ardi Wa La Fi Al-Sama'a

00:00:36.540 --> 00:00:39.100
Assalamu Alaikum Wa Rahmatullahi Wa Barakatuh

00:00:39.100 --> 00:00:43.100
Bismillahir Rahmanir Raheem, Alhamdulillahi Rabbil Aalameen

00:00:43.100 --> 00:00:46.540
Wa Salatu Wa Salamu Ala Al-Mab'uthi Rahmatan Lila Aalameen

00:00:46.540 --> 00:00:50.140
Nabi'ina Muhammadin Wa Ala Aalihi Wa Sahbihi Wa Al-Tabi'ina

00:00:50.140 --> 00:00:53.140
Wa Man Tabi'ahum Bi Ihsanin Ila Yumi Al-Din

00:00:53.140 --> 00:00:56.140
We commence by praising Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:00:56.140 --> 00:01:00.140
sending blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:01:00.440 --> 00:01:03.840
and all his companions, may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them,

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:06.140
may he bless his entire household,

00:01:06.140 --> 00:01:10.340
and may he bless every single one of us and grant us every form of goodness.

00:01:10.340 --> 00:01:14.940
This evening, mashaAllah, we read very powerful verses of Surah Al-An'am,

00:01:14.940 --> 00:01:19.840
where Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has made mention of some of what has occurred

00:01:19.840 --> 00:01:21.540
during the Meccan period,

00:01:21.540 --> 00:01:26.040
and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has comforted Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:01:26.040 --> 00:01:29.140
Perhaps tomorrow we will go through some of these verses,

00:01:29.140 --> 00:01:33.540
and we will see how and when they were revealed.

00:01:33.540 --> 00:01:35.840
Some of them are connected to the persecution

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:40.540
faced by those who accepted Islam early on.

00:01:40.540 --> 00:01:43.440
And as we do know and we learned yesterday,

00:01:43.440 --> 00:01:47.140
the first person to accept the message of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:50.840
was his own wife Khadijah radiallahu anha,

00:01:50.840 --> 00:01:52.740
may Allah be pleased with her.

00:01:52.740 --> 00:01:55.840
And thereafter, we have Ali ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anhu,

00:01:55.840 --> 00:01:58.840
who was only 10 years old, a young boy at the time,

00:01:58.840 --> 00:02:03.140
he was the first boy to accept Islam, the second person to accept Islam.

00:02:03.140 --> 00:02:06.040
He agreed with Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam immediately,

00:02:06.040 --> 00:02:08.940
because they knew the man was truthful,

00:02:08.940 --> 00:02:11.240
they knew the credentials of this man,

00:02:11.240 --> 00:02:15.040
they knew exactly what his standing was,

00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:18.240
and they knew that he was not in a position to come to them

00:02:18.240 --> 00:02:20.140
and to tell them some lies.

00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:25.840
And over and above that, the message itself was so pure, so pristine,

00:02:25.940 --> 00:02:31.340
common sense would be that it is calling towards that which is purity.

00:02:31.340 --> 00:02:34.640
It is not calling towards his own elevation,

00:02:34.640 --> 00:02:38.740
worshipping him, giving him wealth, acknowledging him and so on.

00:02:38.740 --> 00:02:43.940
No, it was to do with the link between a man and his maker.

00:02:43.940 --> 00:02:46.740
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us that link

00:02:46.740 --> 00:02:49.440
and may he make us from those who understand.

00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:54.740
We have thereafter, we made mention of Zayd ibn Harithah radiallahu anhu,

00:02:54.740 --> 00:02:57.840
and how he refused to go back with his parents,

00:02:57.840 --> 00:03:03.040
and instead he decided to remain with Muhammad ibn Abdullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:03:03.040 --> 00:03:05.940
Then the daughters of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:03:05.940 --> 00:03:08.740
we made mention of them, may Allah be pleased with them.

00:03:08.740 --> 00:03:12.440
They too, subhanallah, accepted what their dad had to say,

00:03:12.440 --> 00:03:14.040
their father had to say.

00:03:14.040 --> 00:03:18.540
He was a role model for them from before nubuwa and prophethood.

00:03:18.540 --> 00:03:21.140
He was already the person whom they looked up to,

00:03:21.140 --> 00:03:23.640
they loved him so much, he was upright,

00:03:23.640 --> 00:03:27.140
he had a very, very high standing even in Quraish.

00:03:27.140 --> 00:03:29.640
He was known as as-Sadiq al-Ameen,

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:32.540
the truthful, the trustworthy from the beginning,

00:03:32.540 --> 00:03:35.340
subhanallah, from many, many years before that.

00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:38.440
Then we have Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu.

00:03:38.440 --> 00:03:42.740
For your information, he suffered a lot after accepting Islam.

00:03:42.740 --> 00:03:47.240
At this stage, Islam was only spread by word of mouth

00:03:47.240 --> 00:03:49.740
to particular people who were chosen.

00:03:49.740 --> 00:03:53.940
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala instructed Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:03:53.940 --> 00:03:57.840
to get up and warn those who were the closest to him

00:03:57.840 --> 00:04:01.840
in what was known as the secret call or the call

00:04:01.840 --> 00:04:04.840
which was preliminary, the first call.

00:04:04.840 --> 00:04:07.140
And that Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:04:07.140 --> 00:04:08.540
being one of the best friends,

00:04:08.540 --> 00:04:12.040
if not the best friend of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:14.840
he was spoken to and immediately he surrendered.

00:04:14.840 --> 00:04:16.340
He said, if you are saying this,

00:04:16.340 --> 00:04:19.840
I immediately declare that you are definitely the worshipper

00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:24.640
or the messenger of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala and his worshipper.

00:04:24.640 --> 00:04:27.040
So that was Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu.

00:04:27.040 --> 00:04:30.540
So much so that he was persecuted in Makkah thereafter.

00:04:30.540 --> 00:04:34.340
You see, news started flying and rumors started spreading.

00:04:34.340 --> 00:04:35.940
What was this news and rumor?

00:04:35.940 --> 00:04:37.540
People began to say,

00:04:37.540 --> 00:04:40.540
this man has come with something new

00:04:40.540 --> 00:04:42.040
and news started flying,

00:04:42.040 --> 00:04:44.640
but there was no confirmed news

00:04:44.740 --> 00:04:46.940
in the sense that Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:04:46.940 --> 00:04:49.040
had not declared anything openly,

00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:51.140
but people began to whisper.

00:04:51.140 --> 00:04:54.040
And you and I know that when you tell someone,

00:04:54.040 --> 00:04:55.240
don't tell anyone,

00:04:55.240 --> 00:04:57.840
it's quicker for that type of news to spread

00:04:57.840 --> 00:04:59.540
than when you come out openly with it.

00:04:59.540 --> 00:05:02.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:05:02.140 --> 00:05:05.740
I think we are far worse than the people of that time

00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:07.240
when it comes to spreading rumor

00:05:07.240 --> 00:05:10.040
because we supposed to be believers.

00:05:10.040 --> 00:05:11.640
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:05:11.640 --> 00:05:13.240
we declare him as a Nabi,

00:05:13.240 --> 00:05:16.140
but still we love rumor and we love gossip

00:05:16.140 --> 00:05:17.640
and we love tales

00:05:17.640 --> 00:05:20.440
and mostly it doesn't even affect us.

00:05:20.440 --> 00:05:22.040
It's not connected to us

00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:24.740
and it perhaps is lies in most cases,

00:05:24.740 --> 00:05:27.340
but that makes the juicy iftar

00:05:27.340 --> 00:05:29.140
that we actually spoil our fast with.

00:05:29.140 --> 00:05:30.540
May Allah protect us.

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:31.140
Allahu Akbar.

00:05:31.140 --> 00:05:34.240
Imagine having a dry piece of bread for iftar.

00:05:34.240 --> 00:05:36.940
I think our people know what marination is all about

00:05:36.940 --> 00:05:38.940
and they know what all the spices

00:05:38.940 --> 00:05:40.240
and everything is all about

00:05:40.240 --> 00:05:42.940
in order to give it the spike to make it more tasty.

00:05:42.940 --> 00:05:46.140
Let that not happen in our speech and language

00:05:46.140 --> 00:05:49.040
when it comes to speaking about people.

00:05:49.040 --> 00:05:50.240
May we be upright.

00:05:50.240 --> 00:05:51.640
May we be truthful.

00:05:51.640 --> 00:05:53.840
May we learn to cover the faults of others

00:05:53.840 --> 00:05:56.240
rather than what the West is teaching us today.

00:05:56.240 --> 00:05:57.940
Go out and expose everybody.

00:05:57.940 --> 00:05:58.840
That's the West.

00:05:58.840 --> 00:05:59.940
That's the Western teaching.

00:05:59.940 --> 00:06:02.540
In Islam, we are taught cover people

00:06:02.540 --> 00:06:03.940
and remember make dua for them.

00:06:03.940 --> 00:06:05.440
You want to address a problem,

00:06:05.440 --> 00:06:07.440
go to them and address it directly.

00:06:07.440 --> 00:06:08.940
You don't have to go and spread.

00:06:08.940 --> 00:06:10.640
You spread, other people spread.

00:06:10.640 --> 00:06:14.140
They add spices about you and you add about them.

00:06:14.140 --> 00:06:14.740
What happens?

00:06:14.740 --> 00:06:16.740
Society becomes a bunch of people

00:06:16.740 --> 00:06:18.640
who are just talking about one another.

00:06:18.640 --> 00:06:21.140
So at that particular time,

00:06:21.140 --> 00:06:22.740
there was whisperings.

00:06:22.740 --> 00:06:23.940
Whisperings amongst people

00:06:23.940 --> 00:06:26.040
that there is something going on here.

00:06:26.040 --> 00:06:27.340
Something going on here.

00:06:27.340 --> 00:06:29.140
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:06:29.140 --> 00:06:30.540
accepted the message.

00:06:30.540 --> 00:06:33.440
He did not deny that he accepted the message.

00:06:33.440 --> 00:06:34.540
If someone asked him,

00:06:34.540 --> 00:06:37.340
he would not deny that I have accepted the message

00:06:37.340 --> 00:06:38.440
and there is a message.

00:06:38.440 --> 00:06:40.640
So the news began to spread.

00:06:40.640 --> 00:06:42.040
We have others who accepted.

00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:45.640
We made mention of Umm Aiman radiallahu anhu.

00:06:45.640 --> 00:06:48.940
The one who looked after Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:06:48.940 --> 00:06:50.740
from a very, very early age.

00:06:50.740 --> 00:06:54.040
In fact, from birth, she was already there.

00:06:54.040 --> 00:06:56.540
She was the slave of Amina binti Wahab,

00:06:56.540 --> 00:06:58.840
the mother of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:06:58.840 --> 00:06:59.940
Later on,

00:06:59.940 --> 00:07:03.640
he inherited her from his mother sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:07:03.640 --> 00:07:04.840
and he freed her

00:07:04.840 --> 00:07:09.140
when he married Khadija binti Khuwailid radiallahu anhu.

00:07:09.140 --> 00:07:10.640
And thereafter we see

00:07:10.640 --> 00:07:13.540
that she was one of those who accepted Islam

00:07:13.540 --> 00:07:15.640
primarily right at the beginning.

00:07:15.640 --> 00:07:18.940
We mentioned yesterday that when a man

00:07:18.940 --> 00:07:21.440
has his own family members bear witness

00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:22.640
that he is upright,

00:07:22.640 --> 00:07:23.840
then indeed he is upright

00:07:23.840 --> 00:07:26.740
because your family members see you 24-7.

00:07:26.740 --> 00:07:28.240
Let's ask ourselves,

00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:30.740
are we like that or are we the opposite?

00:07:30.740 --> 00:07:31.740
Sometimes with us,

00:07:31.740 --> 00:07:33.840
everybody thinks we really nice

00:07:33.840 --> 00:07:36.140
and everybody thinks that we are really good people

00:07:36.140 --> 00:07:38.140
and our own wives and children

00:07:38.140 --> 00:07:39.540
are the ones who say,

00:07:39.540 --> 00:07:41.640
this man you don't know his true colors.

00:07:41.640 --> 00:07:42.640
You really don't know.

00:07:42.640 --> 00:07:44.940
He troubles us, he harasses us, he swears.

00:07:44.940 --> 00:07:46.840
When he comes home, he's a different man.

00:07:46.840 --> 00:07:48.440
The minute he answers the phone,

00:07:48.440 --> 00:07:51.340
the tone is such that had he spoken

00:07:51.340 --> 00:07:53.040
with that tone in the house,

00:07:53.040 --> 00:07:54.540
perhaps the love would have increased.

00:07:54.540 --> 00:07:55.440
Allahu Akbar.

00:07:55.440 --> 00:07:57.640
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us

00:07:57.640 --> 00:07:59.440
and grant us every form of lesson.

00:07:59.440 --> 00:08:02.240
This is why Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam's family

00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:03.540
accepted first

00:08:03.540 --> 00:08:05.740
because he was the role model for them

00:08:05.740 --> 00:08:07.440
right from the very beginning.

00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:10.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us conscious of the way

00:08:10.140 --> 00:08:13.040
we treat our own families and family members.

00:08:13.040 --> 00:08:16.140
So Uthman ibn Affan radiallahu anhu

00:08:16.140 --> 00:08:18.340
was one of those who accepted Islam.

00:08:18.340 --> 00:08:20.640
And when his uncle al-Hakam ibn Abi al-'As

00:08:20.640 --> 00:08:24.240
found out that this Uthman ibn Affan ibn Abi al-'As

00:08:24.240 --> 00:08:26.340
has accepted Islam,

00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:27.540
what did his uncle do?

00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:28.440
He went to him and said,

00:08:28.440 --> 00:08:33.440
hey, I am disassociating myself from you completely.

00:08:33.440 --> 00:08:34.740
You will have no link with me.

00:08:34.740 --> 00:08:35.840
You cannot come to me

00:08:35.840 --> 00:08:37.740
and I don't want you to come to us.

00:08:37.740 --> 00:08:39.040
You have nothing to do with us

00:08:39.040 --> 00:08:42.540
unless you disbelieve in Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:08:42.540 --> 00:08:46.940
And Uthman ibn Affan was 34 years old at the time.

00:08:46.940 --> 00:08:48.140
He looked at his uncle and he said,

00:08:48.140 --> 00:08:49.640
oh uncle, do what you want.

00:08:49.640 --> 00:08:50.440
You can cut me.

00:08:50.440 --> 00:08:53.140
You can really disassociate from me.

00:08:53.140 --> 00:08:57.140
I am not going to abandon what Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:08:57.140 --> 00:08:57.940
has come with,

00:08:57.940 --> 00:08:59.840
nor am I going to disbelieve.

00:08:59.840 --> 00:09:02.440
So after some time when his uncle realized

00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:04.940
that this young man is not going to give up anything

00:09:04.940 --> 00:09:07.040
and he was already quite old anyway,

00:09:07.040 --> 00:09:08.240
then they softened up.

00:09:08.240 --> 00:09:12.740
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us such understanding

00:09:12.740 --> 00:09:15.140
that we have so many freedoms

00:09:15.140 --> 00:09:18.140
and we have nobody blocking us and stopping us.

00:09:18.140 --> 00:09:20.540
Why do we still not find ourselves

00:09:20.540 --> 00:09:23.840
obeying Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala's instructions?

00:09:23.840 --> 00:09:26.940
Another example was Az-Zubayr ibn al-'Awwam radiallahu anhu.

00:09:26.940 --> 00:09:29.140
He was only 12 years old

00:09:29.140 --> 00:09:32.640
and his uncle had tied him up

00:09:32.640 --> 00:09:36.740
and they used to smoke him with the smoke of the fire

00:09:36.740 --> 00:09:38.640
and told him as a young boy

00:09:38.640 --> 00:09:40.140
that we want you to leave.

00:09:40.140 --> 00:09:43.240
We want you to disbelieve in Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:09:43.240 --> 00:09:44.240
The young boy,

00:09:44.240 --> 00:09:46.040
he understood from the message

00:09:46.040 --> 00:09:49.640
that here the people are worshipping their sticks and stones and idols

00:09:49.640 --> 00:09:53.340
and here Muhammad ibn Abdullah is calling us to worship our maker.

00:09:53.340 --> 00:09:54.240
He is warning us.

00:09:54.240 --> 00:09:56.240
He is telling us to behave well,

00:09:56.240 --> 00:09:59.040
not to drink, not to commit adultery and so on.

00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:01.040
At that time alcohol was not prohibited yet,

00:10:01.040 --> 00:10:03.540
but there were other rules that were in place

00:10:03.540 --> 00:10:06.740
and subhanallah they were pure and good.

00:10:06.740 --> 00:10:08.540
Young boy understood this.

00:10:08.540 --> 00:10:09.840
He was not the only one.

00:10:09.840 --> 00:10:11.440
Many of these young boys,

00:10:11.440 --> 00:10:13.440
they understood in their teens,

00:10:13.440 --> 00:10:15.040
they understood this

00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:19.040
and they faced persecution from their family members.

00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:20.840
They still did not give it up.

00:10:20.840 --> 00:10:21.840
Subhanallah.

00:10:21.840 --> 00:10:24.940
What were they gaining with Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:10:24.940 --> 00:10:27.540
in terms of material wealth or status?

00:10:27.540 --> 00:10:28.440
Nothing.

00:10:28.440 --> 00:10:31.340
They were gaining nothing in terms of material wealth.

00:10:31.340 --> 00:10:34.140
They were only pure believers.

00:10:34.140 --> 00:10:36.540
They believed in something purely

00:10:36.540 --> 00:10:38.940
and above the persecution,

00:10:38.940 --> 00:10:40.940
they still remained steadfast.

00:10:40.940 --> 00:10:42.040
Subhanallah.

00:10:42.040 --> 00:10:44.940
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala kept him.

00:10:44.940 --> 00:10:47.040
Another one who was 17 years old,

00:10:47.040 --> 00:10:49.740
Sa'd ibn Abi Waqqas radiallahu anhu.

00:10:49.740 --> 00:10:50.740
For your information,

00:10:50.740 --> 00:10:52.740
these that I have mentioned so far,

00:10:52.740 --> 00:10:56.040
they are from the high families of Quraysh.

00:10:56.040 --> 00:10:57.940
They are children of the lofty.

00:10:58.040 --> 00:11:00.640
They are children of people who were well-to-do

00:11:00.640 --> 00:11:03.640
and they had good standings and positions in Quraysh.

00:11:03.640 --> 00:11:06.340
And this is why their parents wanted them back.

00:11:06.340 --> 00:11:08.140
Their family members wanted them back

00:11:08.140 --> 00:11:10.440
because to them it was an insult

00:11:10.440 --> 00:11:12.940
for these children of ours to actually turn.

00:11:12.940 --> 00:11:15.040
Wallahi, I need to stop there for a moment.

00:11:15.040 --> 00:11:16.140
Some of us,

00:11:16.140 --> 00:11:18.340
when we move around with our own daughters

00:11:18.340 --> 00:11:20.340
who want to cover from head to toe,

00:11:20.340 --> 00:11:22.640
we feel so bad to say,

00:11:22.640 --> 00:11:23.840
how can I walk in the mall

00:11:23.840 --> 00:11:25.440
whilst you covered from top to bottom?

00:11:25.440 --> 00:11:27.240
Come on, man, you're still so young.

00:11:27.240 --> 00:11:28.640
How, why are you covering?

00:11:28.640 --> 00:11:31.440
Some of us discourage our own daughters

00:11:31.440 --> 00:11:33.540
when they want to turn to their deen.

00:11:33.540 --> 00:11:36.140
So we are also guilty sometimes.

00:11:36.140 --> 00:11:39.340
Some of us, when our children would like to grow facial hair

00:11:39.340 --> 00:11:41.540
following the example of all the messengers

00:11:41.540 --> 00:11:43.640
including Jesus may peace be upon him,

00:11:43.640 --> 00:11:45.740
then we tend to ban them.

00:11:45.740 --> 00:11:46.840
Ban them completely.

00:11:46.840 --> 00:11:48.040
Say, listen, you know what?

00:11:48.040 --> 00:11:49.540
If you're not going to use this Gillette

00:11:49.540 --> 00:11:51.240
with the shaving cream,

00:11:51.240 --> 00:11:53.540
then you cannot live in this home.

00:11:53.540 --> 00:11:55.240
We don't want you to look so scruffy.

00:11:55.940 --> 00:11:58.240
We call the Sunnah scruffy,

00:11:58.240 --> 00:12:00.240
and yet we claim to be believers.

00:12:00.240 --> 00:12:01.840
So what is the difference between us

00:12:01.840 --> 00:12:03.740
and the kufar of Quraysh?

00:12:03.740 --> 00:12:06.340
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:12:06.340 --> 00:12:07.540
They were embarrassed

00:12:07.540 --> 00:12:08.940
when their children accepted

00:12:08.940 --> 00:12:11.340
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam's message.

00:12:11.340 --> 00:12:13.240
Wallahi, sometimes we become embarrassed

00:12:13.240 --> 00:12:14.340
at the same thing.

00:12:14.340 --> 00:12:15.340
Why should that be?

00:12:15.340 --> 00:12:17.440
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us people

00:12:17.440 --> 00:12:20.140
who are proud of the achievements of our children

00:12:20.140 --> 00:12:22.240
in a way that they can correct us

00:12:22.240 --> 00:12:24.140
and we nod our head when they arrive to say,

00:12:24.140 --> 00:12:26.440
my son, Allah has given you that knowledge.

00:12:26.440 --> 00:12:27.740
You came to me today.

00:12:27.740 --> 00:12:28.740
You told it to me.

00:12:28.740 --> 00:12:31.040
Alhamdulillah, I thank Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:12:31.040 --> 00:12:32.640
for giving me a child like this.

00:12:32.640 --> 00:12:35.040
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:12:35.040 --> 00:12:37.340
Wallahi, what I've said is a serious matter.

00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:38.840
If we are weak, it's one thing.

00:12:38.840 --> 00:12:40.540
But why should we impose that weakness

00:12:40.540 --> 00:12:41.740
on our own children?

00:12:41.740 --> 00:12:43.740
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala forgive us

00:12:43.740 --> 00:12:45.140
and grant us steadfastness.

00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:48.140
So this young boy Sa'd ibn Abi Waqqas radiallahu anhu,

00:12:48.140 --> 00:12:50.440
when his mother found out

00:12:50.440 --> 00:12:51.940
that this son of mine

00:12:51.940 --> 00:12:55.740
has accepted the message of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:12:55.740 --> 00:12:57.140
she went up to him.

00:12:57.140 --> 00:12:58.440
What is it, O Sa'd?

00:12:58.440 --> 00:13:01.140
He declared, yes, it's a fact, it's true.

00:13:01.140 --> 00:13:03.740
They did not deny it.

00:13:03.740 --> 00:13:07.340
So she says, I will stand in the sun, in the heat

00:13:07.340 --> 00:13:09.740
and I will not eat and I will not drink

00:13:09.740 --> 00:13:11.740
and I am not going to move from here

00:13:11.740 --> 00:13:15.140
until you reject Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:15.140 --> 00:13:16.940
and you come back to our idols

00:13:16.940 --> 00:13:19.440
and you come back to the religion of your forefathers

00:13:19.540 --> 00:13:22.140
and you worship these sticks and stones once again.

00:13:22.140 --> 00:13:23.640
What happened to him?

00:13:23.640 --> 00:13:24.540
He was steadfast.

00:13:24.540 --> 00:13:26.240
He says, O my mother, that's up to you.

00:13:26.240 --> 00:13:28.140
I am not going to give up anything.

00:13:28.140 --> 00:13:29.840
So Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:29.840 --> 00:13:33.540
thereafter was asked by Sa'd ibn Abi Waqqas radiallahu anhu

00:13:33.540 --> 00:13:35.540
that look, it's the second day running,

00:13:35.540 --> 00:13:37.840
my mother is still out there.

00:13:37.840 --> 00:13:39.240
It's the third day running,

00:13:39.240 --> 00:13:41.840
my mother is still out there.

00:13:41.840 --> 00:13:44.340
Obviously, there's a link.

00:13:44.340 --> 00:13:45.640
So verses were revealed.

00:13:45.640 --> 00:13:48.940
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala sent down verses.

00:13:48.940 --> 00:13:55.140
wa wasrayna l-insana bi wali dayhi husna

00:13:55.140 --> 00:14:02.140
wa in jahada ka litushrik bi ma laysalaka bi ilmun

00:14:02.140 --> 00:14:06.840
fa la tuti'humaa ilayya marji'ukum

00:14:06.840 --> 00:14:14.840
fa unabbi'ukum bima kuntum ta'maloon

00:14:14.840 --> 00:14:19.540
Allah has instructed you to be very kind to your parents,

00:14:19.540 --> 00:14:21.140
even if they are non-Muslim.

00:14:21.140 --> 00:14:25.640
Allah has instructed you to be very kind to your parents.

00:14:25.640 --> 00:14:27.640
Remember, Allah has chosen your parents

00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:29.340
and my parents for me and you.

00:14:29.340 --> 00:14:31.140
We did not apply for our parents.

00:14:31.140 --> 00:14:35.340
It's Allah's test upon us for having given us

00:14:35.340 --> 00:14:38.540
or by having given us parents whom we have

00:14:38.540 --> 00:14:42.040
because Allah knows that was the means of Him

00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:44.040
bringing us into creation.

00:14:44.040 --> 00:14:47.340
And this is why He says you need to honor that link

00:14:47.340 --> 00:14:48.740
and you need to respect it.

00:14:48.740 --> 00:14:51.740
But there is one exception.

00:14:51.740 --> 00:14:55.540
Whenever they instruct you to engage in polytheism

00:14:55.540 --> 00:14:57.840
or to misbehave spiritually

00:14:57.840 --> 00:15:01.940
or to disobey the commands of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:15:01.940 --> 00:15:04.540
that's the only time you don't obey their instruction.

00:15:04.540 --> 00:15:07.040
Anything to do with the sin, you don't obey them.

00:15:07.040 --> 00:15:08.240
But anything else,

00:15:08.240 --> 00:15:10.740
no matter who your parent is and what they've done

00:15:10.740 --> 00:15:13.640
and whatever has happened and they can be non-Muslim,

00:15:13.640 --> 00:15:16.740
you need to obey their instructions and fulfill their rights

00:15:16.740 --> 00:15:19.440
and you need to make sure you have been kind to them

00:15:19.440 --> 00:15:22.140
and you have looked after them as best as you can

00:15:22.140 --> 00:15:24.540
on condition that they have not instructed you

00:15:24.540 --> 00:15:26.140
to do something sinful.

00:15:26.140 --> 00:15:28.740
And this is why Allah says at the end of those verses

00:15:28.740 --> 00:15:30.740
that you will then return to Allah,

00:15:30.740 --> 00:15:32.140
all of you, both parties.

00:15:32.140 --> 00:15:34.140
Then He will inform you of your deeds

00:15:34.140 --> 00:15:35.640
and what you used to do.

00:15:35.640 --> 00:15:38.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:15:38.140 --> 00:15:39.440
and may He forgive us.

00:15:39.440 --> 00:15:41.540
So when those verses were revealed,

00:15:41.540 --> 00:15:45.240
they gave comfort to Sa'ad ibn Abi Waqqas radiyaAllahu anhu.

00:15:45.240 --> 00:15:46.240
And after some time,

00:15:46.240 --> 00:15:51.040
you find the effects of these people's attitude calmed down.

00:15:51.040 --> 00:15:52.440
And they also calmed down.

00:15:52.440 --> 00:15:55.940
They softened up a little bit because they knew no turning back.

00:15:55.940 --> 00:16:00.840
We don't know of a single person of the early Muslims

00:16:00.840 --> 00:16:04.240
who turned back from their faith, not even one.

00:16:04.240 --> 00:16:06.840
Because why would they have entered in the first place?

00:16:06.840 --> 00:16:10.440
To enter the faith, you needed to have lots of courage.

00:16:10.440 --> 00:16:14.540
You needed to go against your families and your tribe

00:16:14.540 --> 00:16:17.640
and those who were worshipping idols and so on.

00:16:17.640 --> 00:16:20.940
It was easier for Christians to turn to Islam

00:16:20.940 --> 00:16:23.340
because the faith is quite similar.

00:16:23.340 --> 00:16:25.840
But it was very difficult for the people of Quraysh

00:16:25.840 --> 00:16:28.740
because their faith was worlds apart.

00:16:28.740 --> 00:16:29.940
They were worshipping stones.

00:16:29.940 --> 00:16:32.240
They never believed in the life after death.

00:16:32.240 --> 00:16:33.140
They just thought

00:16:33.140 --> 00:16:37.440
ما هي إلا حياتنا الدنيا نموت و نحيا

00:16:37.440 --> 00:16:38.940
It is only this life.

00:16:38.940 --> 00:16:40.340
We are dead, we are alive.

00:16:40.340 --> 00:16:41.940
That's it, so enjoy life.

00:16:41.940 --> 00:16:44.540
Like the attitude of people today.

00:16:44.540 --> 00:16:46.240
You know what's the statement today?

00:16:46.240 --> 00:16:49.040
They say life comes once, so enjoy it.

00:16:49.040 --> 00:16:51.140
Go out and catch as much as you can.

00:16:51.140 --> 00:16:53.540
Life just comes once, you're going to miss out.

00:16:53.540 --> 00:16:56.340
We as Muslims have a different attitude.

00:16:56.340 --> 00:16:57.640
This is your test.

00:16:57.640 --> 00:16:59.840
The ultimate life is yet to come.

00:16:59.840 --> 00:17:02.140
So this is why don't fool around here.

00:17:02.140 --> 00:17:03.940
Otherwise you lose what is to come.

00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:06.340
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala forgive our sins,

00:17:06.340 --> 00:17:08.840
our shortcomings and may He grant us a new chapter.

00:17:08.840 --> 00:17:10.740
Remember, no matter what we've done,

00:17:10.740 --> 00:17:12.440
Allah is غفور الرحيم.

00:17:12.440 --> 00:17:14.040
It is us who need to turn.

00:17:14.040 --> 00:17:16.140
Allah is most forgiving, most merciful.

00:17:16.140 --> 00:17:18.940
We need to turn to Him before it is too late.

00:17:18.940 --> 00:17:20.140
Another example.

00:17:20.140 --> 00:17:22.640
The example of Talhah ibn Ubaydillah

00:17:22.640 --> 00:17:23.540
رضي الله عنه

00:17:23.540 --> 00:17:25.640
He was 13 years old

00:17:25.640 --> 00:17:28.440
and he had heard from some of the rabbis,

00:17:28.440 --> 00:17:32.040
from some of the religious people of the people of the book,

00:17:32.040 --> 00:17:35.040
some of the qualities of a messenger who was going to come.

00:17:35.040 --> 00:17:36.440
So what had happened?

00:17:36.440 --> 00:17:38.540
When Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:17:38.540 --> 00:17:42.240
spoke to this young boy in his early teens,

00:17:42.240 --> 00:17:43.540
he immediately surrendered

00:17:43.540 --> 00:17:44.040
because he said,

00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:45.040
No, I've heard about this.

00:17:45.040 --> 00:17:45.840
I know it's happening.

00:17:45.840 --> 00:17:46.540
It's coming.

00:17:46.540 --> 00:17:48.340
And if it's him, then I am with.

00:17:48.340 --> 00:17:49.540
Subhanallah.

00:17:49.540 --> 00:17:50.540
Imagine early teens.

00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:51.440
Look at our youngsters.

00:17:51.440 --> 00:17:52.240
Masha'Allah.

00:17:52.240 --> 00:17:55.240
These were young people who changed their lives.

00:17:55.240 --> 00:17:57.140
They knew what was right from wrong.

00:17:57.140 --> 00:17:58.140
Subhanallah.

00:17:58.140 --> 00:18:00.640
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala as old as we are,

00:18:00.640 --> 00:18:03.540
grant us the ability to distinguish between right and wrong

00:18:03.540 --> 00:18:05.440
and then to follow that which is right.

00:18:05.440 --> 00:18:09.540
Even if it is against our own whims and fancies and lusts and desires.

00:18:09.540 --> 00:18:12.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us steadfastness.

00:18:12.940 --> 00:18:16.140
Another example was that of Ammar ibn Yasir.

00:18:16.140 --> 00:18:19.640
Ammar ibn Yasir radiallahu anhu and his family.

00:18:19.640 --> 00:18:22.240
They are well known in the history of Islam.

00:18:22.240 --> 00:18:24.440
It was known as Ali Yasir,

00:18:24.440 --> 00:18:26.540
the family of Yasir.

00:18:26.540 --> 00:18:29.540
Yasir was the father and Ammar was the son.

00:18:29.540 --> 00:18:30.940
The mother was known as Sumiyyah,

00:18:30.940 --> 00:18:31.740
the brother as well.

00:18:31.740 --> 00:18:32.440
Subhanallah.

00:18:32.440 --> 00:18:32.940
What happened?

00:18:32.940 --> 00:18:34.540
They accepted Islam

00:18:34.540 --> 00:18:36.740
and they were slaves.

00:18:36.740 --> 00:18:38.240
They were slaves.

00:18:38.240 --> 00:18:39.740
And what had happened?

00:18:39.740 --> 00:18:42.540
Their master began to punish them and penalize them.

00:18:42.540 --> 00:18:44.940
How can you declare the faith of this man

00:18:44.940 --> 00:18:47.440
and stop worshipping the idols and so on?

00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:48.640
Who do you think you are?

00:18:48.640 --> 00:18:50.240
You are still a slave.

00:18:50.240 --> 00:18:52.340
And they started being punished.

00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:54.040
And how were they punished?

00:18:54.040 --> 00:18:57.640
Drawn in the hot desert.

00:18:57.640 --> 00:19:01.440
And what happened was the armor which was made of metal

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:03.440
was made to become so hot

00:19:03.440 --> 00:19:05.440
and then they were made to wear it.

00:19:05.440 --> 00:19:07.840
And on top of that they were left out in the heat.

00:19:07.840 --> 00:19:09.140
They were tortured with fire.

00:19:09.140 --> 00:19:10.540
They were tortured with whips.

00:19:10.540 --> 00:19:12.340
And all they were told was just say

00:19:12.340 --> 00:19:13.940
that I disbelieve in Muhammad.

00:19:13.940 --> 00:19:14.640
That's it.

00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:16.840
There's nothing else that you need to come up with.

00:19:16.840 --> 00:19:19.240
Just say I disbelieve in the one God

00:19:19.240 --> 00:19:22.240
and I want to return to all these idols

00:19:22.240 --> 00:19:23.940
that you people are worshipping.

00:19:23.940 --> 00:19:24.940
They refused.

00:19:24.940 --> 00:19:26.040
So what happened?

00:19:26.040 --> 00:19:27.640
The first martyr,

00:19:27.640 --> 00:19:30.940
the first person to be killed by the kuffar of Quraysh,

00:19:30.940 --> 00:19:33.440
by the disbelievers of Quraysh

00:19:33.440 --> 00:19:36.740
was Sumayyah radiyaAllahu anha, Umm Yasir.

00:19:36.740 --> 00:19:39.240
And it is so bad what they did to her.

00:19:39.240 --> 00:19:41.140
They ripped her apart.

00:19:41.140 --> 00:19:43.540
They literally tore her into pieces.

00:19:43.540 --> 00:19:46.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant her paradise.

00:19:46.140 --> 00:19:48.140
And Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:19:48.140 --> 00:19:49.240
used to pass these people.

00:19:49.240 --> 00:19:50.540
Imagine slaves.

00:19:50.540 --> 00:19:52.640
Today we look at people who are lower than us

00:19:52.640 --> 00:19:53.940
in terms of finance.

00:19:53.940 --> 00:19:55.840
And we think these people are low down

00:19:55.840 --> 00:19:58.040
and you know, perhaps they don't have a standing.

00:19:58.140 --> 00:20:01.240
Wallahi, get one thing right in your mind and mine.

00:20:01.240 --> 00:20:04.740
That is, Allah does not look at your financial standing

00:20:04.740 --> 00:20:07.040
nor does He look at your color or your body.

00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:08.940
He looks at your heart and what is in it.

00:20:08.940 --> 00:20:11.040
Subhanallah.

00:20:11.040 --> 00:20:12.940
So there are people who are saints,

00:20:12.940 --> 00:20:14.040
who are so pious,

00:20:14.040 --> 00:20:16.440
who are the friends of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:20:16.440 --> 00:20:18.440
but they live in huts

00:20:18.440 --> 00:20:22.440
in some of the most remote areas of Africa and elsewhere.

00:20:22.440 --> 00:20:24.040
And yet we may not even know.

00:20:24.040 --> 00:20:26.040
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant them

00:20:26.040 --> 00:20:27.640
goodness and us as well.

00:20:27.640 --> 00:20:29.240
So these people were martyred.

00:20:29.240 --> 00:20:32.040
This lady, this Sumayyah radiallahu anha

00:20:32.040 --> 00:20:34.640
was martyred when Nabi sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:20:34.640 --> 00:20:36.140
passed them.

00:20:36.140 --> 00:20:37.840
He could not utter much.

00:20:37.840 --> 00:20:39.640
They could not help much.

00:20:39.640 --> 00:20:40.240
But he said,

00:20:40.240 --> 00:20:41.840
sabran ala yasir

00:20:41.840 --> 00:20:44.140
fa innama waidakumul jannah

00:20:44.140 --> 00:20:46.740
Bear patience O family of yasir.

00:20:46.740 --> 00:20:49.140
Our appointed time and place is paradise.

00:20:49.140 --> 00:20:50.340
Allahu akbar.

00:20:50.340 --> 00:20:54.340
Imagine, our appointed time and place is paradise.

00:20:54.340 --> 00:20:56.440
Which means just bear it, bear it.

00:20:56.440 --> 00:20:57.640
They bore it.

00:20:57.640 --> 00:20:59.640
The one was martyred, subhanallah.

00:20:59.640 --> 00:21:02.140
What happened to Ammar himself?

00:21:02.140 --> 00:21:03.440
He couldn't bear it.

00:21:03.440 --> 00:21:05.440
They came a stage when they punished him

00:21:05.440 --> 00:21:08.040
and penalized him and he was a young boy

00:21:08.040 --> 00:21:10.440
until he uttered the word.

00:21:10.440 --> 00:21:10.740
He said,

00:21:10.740 --> 00:21:13.440
Okay, I disbelieve in Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:21:13.440 --> 00:21:14.940
He uttered the word.

00:21:14.940 --> 00:21:16.840
So the Muslims were shocked.

00:21:16.840 --> 00:21:19.840
Some of them had the statement in them saying,

00:21:19.840 --> 00:21:21.340
This man has disbelieved.

00:21:21.340 --> 00:21:23.940
This is the first of ours who has disbelieved.

00:21:23.940 --> 00:21:25.440
He's given into pressure.

00:21:25.440 --> 00:21:26.740
He has turned away.

00:21:26.740 --> 00:21:27.540
And do you know what?

00:21:27.540 --> 00:21:29.240
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam said,

00:21:29.240 --> 00:21:32.140
No, his heart is full of conviction.

00:21:32.140 --> 00:21:34.740
He has just uttered a statement by his mouth

00:21:34.740 --> 00:21:36.240
in order to save himself.

00:21:36.240 --> 00:21:37.340
Subhanallah.

00:21:37.340 --> 00:21:40.940
Jibril alayhi sallatu wa sallam came down with verses

00:21:40.940 --> 00:21:42.940
where he clarified,

00:21:42.940 --> 00:21:46.340
Allah had clarified the condition of Ammar ibn yasir

00:21:46.340 --> 00:21:47.840
رضي الله عنه

00:21:47.840 --> 00:21:54.840
من كفر بالله من بعد إيمانه

00:21:54.840 --> 00:22:03.640
إلا من أكره وقلبه مطمئن بالإيمان

00:22:03.640 --> 00:22:09.040
ولكن من شرح بالكفر صدرا

00:22:09.040 --> 00:22:15.610
فعليهم غضب من الله

00:22:15.610 --> 00:22:17.710
Allah is clarifying the difference

00:22:17.710 --> 00:22:20.310
between those who have disbelieved,

00:22:20.310 --> 00:22:22.210
believing in that disbelief

00:22:22.210 --> 00:22:26.410
and those who have uttered a word by their mouths

00:22:26.410 --> 00:22:28.610
in order to protect themselves

00:22:28.610 --> 00:22:31.310
yet their hearts are full of belief.

00:22:31.310 --> 00:22:32.210
Allah says,

00:22:32.210 --> 00:22:34.110
When it gets to a certain point,

00:22:34.110 --> 00:22:35.410
then you need to know

00:22:35.410 --> 00:22:37.410
if you've uttered a word of disbelief

00:22:37.410 --> 00:22:38.910
in order to be protected

00:22:38.910 --> 00:22:40.210
because you could not handle

00:22:40.210 --> 00:22:41.710
what came in your direction

00:22:41.710 --> 00:22:44.810
that does not automatically make you a disbeliever.

00:22:44.910 --> 00:22:47.810
So Ammar ibn yasir رضي الله عنه

00:22:47.810 --> 00:22:50.510
his condition was made clear

00:22:50.510 --> 00:22:53.410
and this is what Allah سبحانه وتعالى revealed.

00:22:53.410 --> 00:22:55.510
Imagine the persecution they went through.

00:22:55.510 --> 00:22:58.210
Imagine what had happened to them سبحان الله

00:22:58.210 --> 00:23:02.910
another example was that of Bilal ibn Rabah رضي الله عنه

00:23:02.910 --> 00:23:04.210
the Abyssinian slave

00:23:04.210 --> 00:23:07.210
who had come to Makkah المكرمة enslaved

00:23:07.210 --> 00:23:10.610
and his master's name was Umayyah ibn Khalaf

00:23:10.610 --> 00:23:13.110
one of the biggest enemies of Islam

00:23:13.110 --> 00:23:15.210
one of the leaders of Quraysh

00:23:15.210 --> 00:23:17.610
when he found out that this little slave of mine

00:23:17.610 --> 00:23:19.610
has accepted the message of Muhammad

00:23:19.610 --> 00:23:23.110
imagine now this was a person

00:23:23.110 --> 00:23:26.210
who was a little bit lower down in the social standing

00:23:26.210 --> 00:23:28.510
but one of the highest in the spiritual standing

00:23:28.510 --> 00:23:29.410
سبحان الله

00:23:29.410 --> 00:23:30.910
you know some people say

00:23:30.910 --> 00:23:34.310
that the early believers were all weak and downtrodden

00:23:34.310 --> 00:23:35.310
no that's not true

00:23:35.310 --> 00:23:37.410
there were a few people who might have been weak

00:23:37.410 --> 00:23:39.610
but the bulk of them were wealthy

00:23:39.610 --> 00:23:42.910
well-to-do people from wealthy families at least

00:23:42.910 --> 00:23:46.210
even if themselves they may not have been as wealthy

00:23:46.210 --> 00:23:47.210
or the wealthiest

00:23:47.210 --> 00:23:49.510
but they were from the best of families

00:23:49.510 --> 00:23:51.610
and this is what we need to understand

00:23:51.610 --> 00:23:53.210
not all of them were weak

00:23:53.210 --> 00:23:55.010
but there were some who were slaves

00:23:55.010 --> 00:23:56.410
a few a handful of them

00:23:56.410 --> 00:23:59.310
like Bilal ibn Rabah رضي الله عنه

00:23:59.310 --> 00:24:00.810
what happened to him

00:24:00.810 --> 00:24:02.910
the same thing they took him out in the desert

00:24:02.910 --> 00:24:04.310
the boulders were made hot

00:24:04.310 --> 00:24:07.310
and he was dragged in these rocks and stones

00:24:07.310 --> 00:24:08.610
and sand of the desert

00:24:08.610 --> 00:24:10.910
and big boulders were put up onto his chest

00:24:10.910 --> 00:24:12.510
and he was whipped and lashed

00:24:12.510 --> 00:24:14.510
one after the other he bled

00:24:14.510 --> 00:24:17.610
and he was being told disbelief in Muhammad

00:24:17.610 --> 00:24:19.910
and he was one of those who was solid

00:24:19.910 --> 00:24:21.810
one of the most powerful

00:24:21.810 --> 00:24:24.510
when it comes to declaring his conviction

00:24:24.510 --> 00:24:26.410
that there is only one God

00:24:26.410 --> 00:24:27.310
only one

00:24:27.310 --> 00:24:30.310
the message was a message of worshiping one Allah

00:24:30.310 --> 00:24:31.610
so he kept on repeating

00:24:31.610 --> 00:24:34.010
أَحَدٌ أَحَدٌ

00:24:34.010 --> 00:24:35.110
there is only one

00:24:35.110 --> 00:24:36.110
one God

00:24:36.110 --> 00:24:36.510
one God

00:24:36.510 --> 00:24:38.310
your idols mean nothing

00:24:38.310 --> 00:24:39.410
it's only one God

00:24:39.410 --> 00:24:40.010
one Allah

00:24:40.010 --> 00:24:40.510
one

00:24:40.510 --> 00:24:41.010
one

00:24:41.010 --> 00:24:42.010
he kept on repeating

00:24:42.010 --> 00:24:42.410
one

00:24:42.410 --> 00:24:42.810
one

00:24:42.810 --> 00:24:43.710
and he was lashed

00:24:43.710 --> 00:24:44.610
and he was whipped

00:24:44.610 --> 00:24:45.810
and he was beaten

00:24:45.810 --> 00:24:48.210
and it continued until one day

00:24:48.210 --> 00:24:50.410
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq رضي الله عنه

00:24:50.410 --> 00:24:52.710
who was a good businessman

00:24:52.710 --> 00:24:54.710
he spent all his wealth

00:24:54.710 --> 00:24:58.010
buying back the slaves from people

00:24:58.010 --> 00:25:00.110
who were punishing those slaves

00:25:00.110 --> 00:25:01.610
who had accepted Islam

00:25:01.610 --> 00:25:02.810
Subhanallah

00:25:02.810 --> 00:25:03.810
so he made money

00:25:03.810 --> 00:25:04.510
he spent it

00:25:04.510 --> 00:25:05.210
to do what

00:25:05.210 --> 00:25:07.010
buying back a slave from a person

00:25:07.010 --> 00:25:08.010
for what reason

00:25:08.010 --> 00:25:09.910
just to free them for the sake of Allah

00:25:10.910 --> 00:25:12.810
so that they are not punished anymore

00:25:12.810 --> 00:25:15.510
how many of us can even spend our money

00:25:15.510 --> 00:25:16.510
when we say our money

00:25:16.510 --> 00:25:17.510
remember one thing

00:25:17.510 --> 00:25:19.510
my beloved brothers and sisters

00:25:19.510 --> 00:25:20.910
the Zakah

00:25:20.910 --> 00:25:22.210
that we give out

00:25:22.210 --> 00:25:23.710
does not belong to us

00:25:23.710 --> 00:25:25.310
that is Allah's wealth

00:25:25.310 --> 00:25:26.810
we have just

00:25:26.810 --> 00:25:28.410
placed it where it belongs

00:25:28.410 --> 00:25:29.810
by giving it out

00:25:29.810 --> 00:25:31.910
those compulsory charities

00:25:31.910 --> 00:25:33.210
as we call them as Muslims

00:25:33.210 --> 00:25:35.210
Zakah

00:25:35.210 --> 00:25:36.110
we have to give them

00:25:36.110 --> 00:25:37.410
whether we like it or not

00:25:37.410 --> 00:25:38.710
doesn't belong to us

00:25:38.810 --> 00:25:40.110
it belongs to the Almighty

00:25:40.110 --> 00:25:41.210
all we have done

00:25:41.210 --> 00:25:42.910
we've taken it as an Amana

00:25:42.910 --> 00:25:43.810
as a trust

00:25:43.810 --> 00:25:46.110
and we've put it where it belongs

00:25:46.110 --> 00:25:48.210
but what is counted

00:25:48.210 --> 00:25:50.610
is the fact that we were upright

00:25:50.610 --> 00:25:51.810
and we were truthful

00:25:51.810 --> 00:25:53.710
now if you really want to engage

00:25:53.710 --> 00:25:55.310
in monetary charities

00:25:55.310 --> 00:25:56.810
give something

00:25:56.810 --> 00:25:58.610
that is from your own wealth

00:25:58.610 --> 00:26:00.210
that you don't owe

00:26:00.210 --> 00:26:01.910
but give out Sadaqatun Lillahat

00:26:01.910 --> 00:26:02.810
as we call them

00:26:02.810 --> 00:26:04.210
something for the sake of Allah

00:26:04.210 --> 00:26:05.410
from your own heart

00:26:05.410 --> 00:26:06.610
not that it was compulsory

00:26:06.610 --> 00:26:07.610
so you gave it

00:26:07.610 --> 00:26:08.610
give out more than that

00:26:08.610 --> 00:26:09.910
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:26:09.910 --> 00:26:10.810
open our doors

00:26:10.810 --> 00:26:13.110
this Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:26:13.110 --> 00:26:14.610
he did not have to do this

00:26:14.610 --> 00:26:15.710
he was one of those

00:26:15.710 --> 00:26:17.410
most generous people

00:26:17.410 --> 00:26:20.410
he loved helping people in need

00:26:20.410 --> 00:26:21.810
and when it came to Islam

00:26:21.810 --> 00:26:24.010
imagine what type of need there was

00:26:24.010 --> 00:26:25.810
so Bilal ibn Rabah one day

00:26:25.810 --> 00:26:28.410
was being punished by Umayyah ibn Khalaf

00:26:28.410 --> 00:26:32.010
and Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:26:32.010 --> 00:26:33.310
was passing

00:26:33.310 --> 00:26:35.510
and he says, oh Umayyah

00:26:35.510 --> 00:26:37.010
aren't you ashamed of what you are doing

00:26:37.010 --> 00:26:38.010
to this slave

00:26:38.010 --> 00:26:39.210
a young boy helpless

00:26:39.210 --> 00:26:40.410
what are you doing to him

00:26:40.410 --> 00:26:41.410
so Umayyah says

00:26:41.410 --> 00:26:42.810
you are the one who spoiled him

00:26:42.810 --> 00:26:44.310
meaning you are also a believer

00:26:44.310 --> 00:26:45.110
just like him

00:26:45.110 --> 00:26:46.210
you spoiled him

00:26:46.210 --> 00:26:47.110
he says

00:26:47.110 --> 00:26:48.810
what will you do to save him

00:26:48.810 --> 00:26:50.710
so Abu Bakr radiallahu anhu says

00:26:50.710 --> 00:26:51.610
you sell him to me

00:26:51.610 --> 00:26:52.710
he says I will sell him

00:26:52.710 --> 00:26:53.910
here is the price

00:26:53.910 --> 00:26:55.110
take him free the man

00:26:55.110 --> 00:26:55.910
the man was free

00:26:55.910 --> 00:26:57.010
subhanallah

00:26:57.010 --> 00:26:58.310
subhanallah

00:26:58.310 --> 00:27:01.110
look at Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:27:01.110 --> 00:27:03.210
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:27:03.210 --> 00:27:06.410
had guaranteed him a place in paradise already

00:27:06.410 --> 00:27:07.410
before he died

00:27:07.410 --> 00:27:08.810
well before he died

00:27:08.810 --> 00:27:10.010
it was already told

00:27:10.010 --> 00:27:11.010
a group of people

00:27:11.010 --> 00:27:12.610
a certain number of people

00:27:12.610 --> 00:27:14.410
were already told

00:27:14.410 --> 00:27:16.610
that you are from amongst those in paradise

00:27:16.610 --> 00:27:19.810
from amongst them was the same African slave

00:27:19.810 --> 00:27:21.310
Bilal ibn Rabah

00:27:21.310 --> 00:27:23.610
Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam told him

00:27:23.610 --> 00:27:25.510
when he came back from Mi'raj

00:27:25.510 --> 00:27:27.010
when he came back from the ascension

00:27:27.010 --> 00:27:28.410
he says, oh Bilal

00:27:28.410 --> 00:27:31.010
I have heard your footsteps in paradise

00:27:31.010 --> 00:27:32.110
subhanallah

00:27:32.110 --> 00:27:33.410
inshallah we will get to that

00:27:33.410 --> 00:27:35.510
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us

00:27:35.510 --> 00:27:37.710
and strengthen us

00:27:37.710 --> 00:27:41.210
so that was the example of Bilal ibn Rabah radiallahu anhu

00:27:41.210 --> 00:27:43.510
you have another example of Abdullah ibn Mas'ud

00:27:43.510 --> 00:27:44.310
radiallahu anhu

00:27:44.310 --> 00:27:46.210
we hear his name so many times

00:27:46.210 --> 00:27:47.610
with so many ahadith

00:27:47.610 --> 00:27:48.610
and we hear his name

00:27:48.610 --> 00:27:51.410
when it comes even to the tafseer of the Quran

00:27:51.410 --> 00:27:53.910
and we hear that he was an expert in recitation

00:27:53.910 --> 00:27:55.510
in tafseer, in hadith

00:27:55.510 --> 00:27:58.910
he was an expert in deen at large obviously

00:27:58.910 --> 00:28:00.510
subhanallah radiallahu anhu

00:28:00.510 --> 00:28:02.010
may Allah be pleased with him

00:28:02.010 --> 00:28:03.310
what was he doing?

00:28:03.410 --> 00:28:06.710
he was a young man who was a shepherd

00:28:06.710 --> 00:28:11.010
he used to heard the flock of the leaders of Quraysh

00:28:11.010 --> 00:28:16.610
and when he saw some clear signs

00:28:16.610 --> 00:28:19.110
in that which Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:28:19.110 --> 00:28:21.510
was calling towards

00:28:21.510 --> 00:28:23.910
and when he heard the message of goodness

00:28:23.910 --> 00:28:27.710
and he heard that the message is all about fulfilling your duty

00:28:27.710 --> 00:28:28.810
being a good person

00:28:28.810 --> 00:28:30.010
being upright

00:28:30.010 --> 00:28:31.510
being noble

00:28:31.510 --> 00:28:34.510
not lying, not cheating, not stealing, not deceiving

00:28:34.510 --> 00:28:37.810
not committing adultery, not swearing and so on

00:28:37.810 --> 00:28:39.610
he immediately accepted it

00:28:39.610 --> 00:28:42.410
and he became from amongst the muslimin

00:28:42.410 --> 00:28:44.510
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala strengthen them all

00:28:44.510 --> 00:28:46.210
and grant us also goodness

00:28:46.210 --> 00:28:48.910
and another very interesting story

00:28:48.910 --> 00:28:54.510
a man known very commonly as Abu Dhar al-Ghifari radiallahu anhu

00:28:54.510 --> 00:28:56.710
from a place known as Ghifar

00:28:56.710 --> 00:28:59.510
Ghifar between Mecca and Al-Sham

00:28:59.510 --> 00:29:02.010
going up to the Syrian region

00:29:02.010 --> 00:29:04.510
as we had mentioned Al-Sham

00:29:04.510 --> 00:29:07.710
there is a place not very far from Mecca known as Ghifar

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:10.910
that's where they used to pass from with their caravans

00:29:10.910 --> 00:29:14.510
so he heard that there is a messenger in Mecca

00:29:14.510 --> 00:29:16.510
and this is what he is uttering

00:29:16.510 --> 00:29:18.110
so he tells his brother Unais

00:29:18.110 --> 00:29:21.410
he says oh my brother you know what we've heard this

00:29:21.410 --> 00:29:23.910
pack a little bit of provision for yourself

00:29:23.910 --> 00:29:27.110
go to Mecca and listen to what this man has to say

00:29:27.110 --> 00:29:28.610
and bring back some news

00:29:28.610 --> 00:29:30.810
so the brother went to Mecca quietly

00:29:30.810 --> 00:29:33.310
and he listened to what Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:29:33.310 --> 00:29:34.110
had to say

00:29:34.110 --> 00:29:36.510
and thereafter he went back to Ghifar

00:29:36.510 --> 00:29:38.010
and he spoke to Abu Dhar

00:29:38.010 --> 00:29:41.710
and Abu Dhar his name was Jundub ibn Junada radiallahu anhu

00:29:41.710 --> 00:29:44.210
that was his proper name Jundub ibn Junada

00:29:44.210 --> 00:29:45.510
they used to call him Abu Dhar

00:29:45.510 --> 00:29:46.610
as we mentioned yesterday

00:29:46.610 --> 00:29:50.710
Abdullah ibn Uthman is the name of Abu Bakr al-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:29:50.710 --> 00:29:52.310
but it's just that sometimes

00:29:52.310 --> 00:29:54.610
these names became more common

00:29:54.610 --> 00:29:55.510
known as a kuniya

00:29:55.510 --> 00:29:57.810
known as person father of or mother of

00:29:57.810 --> 00:29:59.610
so and so it becomes more common

00:29:59.610 --> 00:30:03.110
so Abu Dhar al-Ghifari heard his brother and said no no no no

00:30:03.110 --> 00:30:04.110
that's not enough

00:30:04.110 --> 00:30:05.610
what you are telling me

00:30:05.610 --> 00:30:07.110
I need more than this

00:30:07.110 --> 00:30:10.010
let me pack my own little provisions and go

00:30:10.010 --> 00:30:13.610
so obviously he was told by his brother of the condition in Mecca

00:30:13.610 --> 00:30:15.610
that you see the Quraish there

00:30:15.610 --> 00:30:18.410
they are really persecuting those who have believed

00:30:18.410 --> 00:30:20.310
so just mind your step

00:30:20.310 --> 00:30:23.610
so Abu Dhar al-Ghifari radiallahu anhu went to Mecca

00:30:23.610 --> 00:30:25.010
he got to the Kaaba

00:30:25.010 --> 00:30:27.310
and he didn't want to ask anyone

00:30:27.410 --> 00:30:29.310
who is Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:30:29.310 --> 00:30:31.710
because he said just now I asked the wrong person

00:30:31.710 --> 00:30:33.610
and I'm in trouble

00:30:33.610 --> 00:30:36.110
so he decided to wait for a while

00:30:36.110 --> 00:30:37.710
according to one of the narrations

00:30:37.710 --> 00:30:41.210
and looking around and seeing and nightfall came

00:30:41.210 --> 00:30:42.310
and he was still watching

00:30:42.310 --> 00:30:44.910
and Ali ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anhu saw this man

00:30:44.910 --> 00:30:47.610
and recognized that this man is not from here

00:30:47.610 --> 00:30:49.810
so he says come I give you a bedding you can sleep

00:30:49.810 --> 00:30:51.910
so he gave him a bedding

00:30:51.910 --> 00:30:53.710
and he spent the night there

00:30:53.710 --> 00:30:55.810
and the following day he packed his provisions again

00:30:55.810 --> 00:30:58.610
and he went back to that area around the Kaaba

00:30:58.610 --> 00:31:00.210
and he spent a while

00:31:00.210 --> 00:31:03.110
now at that time the pagan Arabs

00:31:03.110 --> 00:31:05.810
they had lots of

00:31:05.810 --> 00:31:08.510
meaning some of the good qualities that they had

00:31:08.510 --> 00:31:09.910
was hospitality

00:31:09.910 --> 00:31:11.310
entertaining the guests

00:31:11.310 --> 00:31:13.810
they would not ask people for three days

00:31:13.810 --> 00:31:16.110
they wouldn't ask that

00:31:16.110 --> 00:31:18.010
why have you come here

00:31:18.010 --> 00:31:19.910
with us we have a habit

00:31:19.910 --> 00:31:21.010
when you came

00:31:21.010 --> 00:31:23.010
and what's the next question

00:31:23.010 --> 00:31:25.010
when you're going you see everybody's laughing here

00:31:25.010 --> 00:31:26.310
when you came and when you're going

00:31:26.310 --> 00:31:28.310
mashaAllah I hope that is asked with a good heart

00:31:28.310 --> 00:31:29.810
because you want to help a person

00:31:29.810 --> 00:31:31.610
you know go nicely alhamdulillah

00:31:31.610 --> 00:31:33.210
but what happens is

00:31:33.210 --> 00:31:35.410
with them they didn't used to ask a question

00:31:35.410 --> 00:31:36.910
why you came

00:31:36.910 --> 00:31:37.510
no

00:31:37.510 --> 00:31:38.410
when are you going

00:31:38.410 --> 00:31:38.810
no

00:31:38.810 --> 00:31:40.110
three days later

00:31:40.110 --> 00:31:42.710
it was their right to ask look why have you come here

00:31:42.710 --> 00:31:43.610
because they believe that

00:31:43.610 --> 00:31:45.510
and Islam for your information

00:31:45.510 --> 00:31:47.410
reiterated that goodness

00:31:47.410 --> 00:31:49.010
and said even as Muslims

00:31:49.010 --> 00:31:49.910
for three days

00:31:49.910 --> 00:31:51.110
your guest has a right

00:31:51.110 --> 00:31:52.110
thereafter

00:31:52.110 --> 00:31:53.010
alhamdulillah

00:31:53.010 --> 00:31:54.410
you can ask them questions

00:31:54.410 --> 00:31:57.110
and you can even begin to charge them for your hospitality

00:31:57.110 --> 00:31:58.310
you know up to very recently

00:31:58.310 --> 00:31:59.710
those who've been for Hajj

00:31:59.710 --> 00:32:00.810
in the 60s and so on

00:32:00.810 --> 00:32:01.910
they will tell you

00:32:01.910 --> 00:32:03.110
that in Saudi Arabia

00:32:03.110 --> 00:32:04.410
those who used to go for Hajj

00:32:04.410 --> 00:32:06.410
in the 1960s and earlier

00:32:06.410 --> 00:32:09.310
nobody asked them for three days

00:32:09.310 --> 00:32:10.610
to pay anything

00:32:10.610 --> 00:32:11.910
the Muallim that was there

00:32:11.910 --> 00:32:13.110
you could stay with him

00:32:13.110 --> 00:32:14.410
and three days later

00:32:14.410 --> 00:32:15.210
you had to decide

00:32:15.210 --> 00:32:17.010
whether you wanted to be there or not

00:32:17.010 --> 00:32:17.610
perhaps

00:32:17.610 --> 00:32:18.510
they started charging

00:32:18.510 --> 00:32:20.610
because of some wise cracks like us

00:32:20.610 --> 00:32:21.610
we go here three days

00:32:21.610 --> 00:32:22.910
when we see we've overstayed here

00:32:22.910 --> 00:32:24.710
we go to another man's place for three days

00:32:24.710 --> 00:32:26.010
when we see we've overstayed there

00:32:26.010 --> 00:32:27.510
we go to another man's for three days

00:32:27.510 --> 00:32:28.610
until the Hajj is over

00:32:28.610 --> 00:32:29.910
so I think to cover that

00:32:29.910 --> 00:32:30.810
we're charged

00:32:30.810 --> 00:32:32.210
even before we arrive

00:32:32.210 --> 00:32:33.210
have you noticed that now?

00:32:33.210 --> 00:32:34.010
MashaAllah

00:32:34.010 --> 00:32:35.410
may Allah protect us

00:32:35.410 --> 00:32:36.810
and may He make it easy for us

00:32:36.810 --> 00:32:37.910
Allahu Akbar

00:32:37.910 --> 00:32:38.710
you missed your flight

00:32:38.710 --> 00:32:39.310
you dead meat

00:32:39.310 --> 00:32:39.810
why?

00:32:39.810 --> 00:32:40.610
you didn't arrive

00:32:40.610 --> 00:32:41.610
but your money's gone

00:32:41.610 --> 00:32:42.710
Allahu Akbar

00:32:42.710 --> 00:32:44.910
not only for the flight that you're going to have to pay

00:32:44.910 --> 00:32:45.710
now for the new one

00:32:45.710 --> 00:32:46.210
but

00:32:46.210 --> 00:32:48.510
even for the day that you didn't stay

00:32:48.510 --> 00:32:49.810
they tell you money's gone

00:32:49.810 --> 00:32:50.610
and on top of that

00:32:50.610 --> 00:32:52.710
your accommodation was given to someone else

00:32:52.710 --> 00:32:53.610
have you heard this?

00:32:53.610 --> 00:32:54.810
I'm sure those who've been

00:32:54.810 --> 00:32:56.510
it sounds all too common to them

00:32:56.510 --> 00:32:58.010
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:32:58.010 --> 00:32:59.810
grant us hospitality

00:32:59.810 --> 00:33:01.010
may He make us from those

00:33:01.010 --> 00:33:02.110
who stand upright

00:33:02.110 --> 00:33:02.710
really

00:33:02.710 --> 00:33:04.010
and may He make us from those

00:33:04.010 --> 00:33:05.710
who realize and learn a lesson

00:33:05.710 --> 00:33:06.710
even if it means

00:33:06.710 --> 00:33:08.510
learning a lesson from the ignorant

00:33:08.510 --> 00:33:10.010
where they are correct

00:33:10.010 --> 00:33:11.210
if they are correct

00:33:11.210 --> 00:33:12.610
subhanallah

00:33:12.610 --> 00:33:13.310
so

00:33:13.310 --> 00:33:14.410
Ali ibn Abi Talib

00:33:14.410 --> 00:33:15.210
the third day

00:33:15.210 --> 00:33:16.610
he asks Abu Dhar

00:33:16.610 --> 00:33:19.210
can I ask you why you are here?

00:33:19.210 --> 00:33:20.610
so Abu Dhar al-Ghifari

00:33:20.610 --> 00:33:21.810
radiallahu anhu

00:33:21.810 --> 00:33:22.510
he says

00:33:22.510 --> 00:33:24.410
if you promise me

00:33:24.410 --> 00:33:26.310
that you're not going to harm me

00:33:26.310 --> 00:33:27.310
and if you promise me

00:33:27.310 --> 00:33:28.510
that I'm safe and secure

00:33:28.510 --> 00:33:30.410
by telling you why I'm here

00:33:30.410 --> 00:33:32.110
then I can let you know

00:33:32.110 --> 00:33:33.610
so he says I promise

00:33:33.610 --> 00:33:34.810
he says I have heard

00:33:34.810 --> 00:33:35.810
there is a messenger

00:33:35.810 --> 00:33:37.510
who calls towards goodness

00:33:37.510 --> 00:33:39.910
he calls towards worshiping one Allah

00:33:39.910 --> 00:33:41.910
he calls towards abandoning the idols

00:33:41.910 --> 00:33:44.010
he calls towards respect of parents

00:33:44.010 --> 00:33:45.710
he calls towards being upright

00:33:45.710 --> 00:33:47.010
and fulfilling the rights

00:33:47.010 --> 00:33:49.710
he calls towards the banning of

00:33:49.710 --> 00:33:51.610
burying girls and women alive

00:33:51.610 --> 00:33:53.710
he calls towards the banning of

00:33:53.710 --> 00:33:56.510
the maltreatment of women and so on

00:33:56.510 --> 00:33:58.510
so I have come to see him

00:33:58.510 --> 00:34:01.110
and to pledge allegiance with him

00:34:01.110 --> 00:34:02.310
so Ali ibn Abi Talib

00:34:02.310 --> 00:34:04.410
radiallahu anhu told him

00:34:04.410 --> 00:34:06.210
he is indeed a messenger

00:34:06.210 --> 00:34:07.210
and yes

00:34:07.210 --> 00:34:09.210
he is in our midst

00:34:09.210 --> 00:34:10.810
how fortunate was this man

00:34:10.810 --> 00:34:12.910
he arrived at the right man's place

00:34:12.910 --> 00:34:14.910
so he said tomorrow morning

00:34:14.910 --> 00:34:15.910
you follow me

00:34:15.910 --> 00:34:17.910
we don't want people to see you with me

00:34:17.910 --> 00:34:19.010
but you follow me

00:34:19.010 --> 00:34:20.110
if there is any harm

00:34:20.210 --> 00:34:22.810
I'll pretend like I'm pouring some water

00:34:22.810 --> 00:34:24.510
if I pretend like I'm pouring some water

00:34:24.510 --> 00:34:25.810
you know that now you don't follow me

00:34:25.810 --> 00:34:27.010
you can head in your own direction

00:34:27.010 --> 00:34:28.710
but if there is no harm

00:34:28.710 --> 00:34:30.010
you follow me and I'll take you

00:34:30.010 --> 00:34:31.610
all the way to this place

00:34:31.610 --> 00:34:32.710
and you'll meet him

00:34:32.710 --> 00:34:33.910
so Subhanallah

00:34:33.910 --> 00:34:35.110
the following day

00:34:35.110 --> 00:34:36.210
that's exactly what happened

00:34:36.210 --> 00:34:37.910
the two of them followed each other

00:34:37.910 --> 00:34:38.610
and Masha'Allah

00:34:38.610 --> 00:34:39.810
they arrived

00:34:39.810 --> 00:34:41.110
in the presence of Rasulullah

00:34:41.110 --> 00:34:42.610
sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:34:42.610 --> 00:34:43.910
Abu Dharr al-Ghifari

00:34:43.910 --> 00:34:45.510
radiallahu anhu heard

00:34:45.510 --> 00:34:47.310
as he entered words of Muhammad

00:34:47.310 --> 00:34:49.210
sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:34:49.210 --> 00:34:50.810
and he broke down

00:34:50.810 --> 00:34:53.210
and immediately declared his Shahadah

00:34:53.210 --> 00:34:55.110
I bear witness that there is no god but Allah

00:34:55.110 --> 00:34:57.910
and I bear witness that Muhammad is His servant and His messenger

00:34:57.910 --> 00:35:00.210
and he told Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:35:00.210 --> 00:35:01.810
where he had come from

00:35:01.810 --> 00:35:02.910
and what had happened

00:35:02.910 --> 00:35:04.510
and Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:35:04.510 --> 00:35:05.810
made a dua for him

00:35:05.810 --> 00:35:07.510
and told him go back to your people

00:35:07.510 --> 00:35:08.510
and wait there

00:35:08.510 --> 00:35:10.610
until you hear of me

00:35:10.610 --> 00:35:11.710
you know

00:35:11.710 --> 00:35:14.910
in a way that will be much more open than this

00:35:14.910 --> 00:35:17.110
and in a short period of time

00:35:17.110 --> 00:35:20.410
the open call had taken place

00:35:20.410 --> 00:35:23.410
and news spread across the entire peninsula

00:35:23.410 --> 00:35:24.310
Subhanallah

00:35:24.310 --> 00:35:26.410
there is a history of what happened to Ghifar

00:35:26.410 --> 00:35:27.310
Allahu Akbar

00:35:27.310 --> 00:35:29.610
the dua of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:35:29.610 --> 00:35:31.210
Abu Dharr al-Ghifari

00:35:31.210 --> 00:35:33.110
members of his family accepted Islam

00:35:33.110 --> 00:35:35.110
members of his clan accepted Islam

00:35:35.110 --> 00:35:38.010
they went back to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam later on

00:35:38.010 --> 00:35:40.410
perhaps inshallah we will get there at that stage

00:35:40.410 --> 00:35:41.810
so this was

00:35:41.810 --> 00:35:43.110
the plight of the people

00:35:43.110 --> 00:35:45.110
the condition of the people who came

00:35:45.210 --> 00:35:47.810
even during this period of silence

00:35:47.810 --> 00:35:50.310
where they came from afar

00:35:50.310 --> 00:35:51.710
to look for the truth

00:35:51.710 --> 00:35:52.910
and they found it

00:35:52.910 --> 00:35:55.710
and they adopted it and accepted it

00:35:55.710 --> 00:35:57.210
we have also

00:35:57.210 --> 00:36:00.110
the others whom we need to make mention of

00:36:00.110 --> 00:36:01.610
in fact Abu Dharr al-Ghifari

00:36:01.610 --> 00:36:03.510
we are not yet completed with the story

00:36:03.510 --> 00:36:05.910
there is a point that is made mention of where

00:36:05.910 --> 00:36:07.610
when he was so excited

00:36:07.610 --> 00:36:10.910
that he had accepted Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam's call

00:36:10.910 --> 00:36:12.410
he went out by the Kaaba

00:36:12.410 --> 00:36:13.410
and made the announcement

00:36:13.410 --> 00:36:16.110
I bear witness that there is only one

00:36:16.110 --> 00:36:18.710
there is only Allah worthy of worship

00:36:18.710 --> 00:36:19.610
no one else

00:36:19.610 --> 00:36:22.410
and I bear witness that Muhammad is his messenger

00:36:22.410 --> 00:36:24.410
sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:36:24.410 --> 00:36:26.710
the people of Quraysh began to beat him up

00:36:26.710 --> 00:36:27.710
then

00:36:27.710 --> 00:36:29.310
they started beating him up so much

00:36:29.310 --> 00:36:30.410
that they made him bleed

00:36:30.410 --> 00:36:31.610
according to one narration

00:36:31.610 --> 00:36:33.510
Al-Abbas ibn Abdul Muttalib got up

00:36:33.510 --> 00:36:34.810
and told the people of Quraysh

00:36:34.810 --> 00:36:35.910
hey hang on

00:36:35.910 --> 00:36:37.610
this man is from Ghifar

00:36:37.610 --> 00:36:39.510
do you know where Ghifar is?

00:36:39.510 --> 00:36:42.310
Ghifar comes on the way to Sham

00:36:42.410 --> 00:36:45.010
we pass there with our caravans and our wealth

00:36:45.010 --> 00:36:47.510
we are going to be really in big trouble

00:36:47.510 --> 00:36:49.810
if we have made this man suffer here

00:36:49.810 --> 00:36:50.610
you'd better stop

00:36:50.610 --> 00:36:51.910
and that's when they stopped

00:36:51.910 --> 00:36:52.610
Subhanallah

00:36:52.610 --> 00:36:53.310
imagine

00:36:53.310 --> 00:36:55.310
their wealth was more important than anything else

00:36:55.310 --> 00:36:56.110
they knew

00:36:56.110 --> 00:36:57.710
we are now going to pass on our own

00:36:57.710 --> 00:36:59.710
with this caravan going past Ghifar

00:36:59.710 --> 00:37:01.110
there's going to be an issue

00:37:01.110 --> 00:37:02.710
so that is why they stopped

00:37:02.710 --> 00:37:06.310
then we have the others just to mention some of the names

00:37:06.310 --> 00:37:08.710
we have Abdur Rahman ibn Awf radiallahu anhu

00:37:08.710 --> 00:37:11.710
Abu Ubaidah, Amir ibn Al-Jarrah radiallahu anhu

00:37:11.710 --> 00:37:13.310
Uthman ibn Maz'oon

00:37:13.310 --> 00:37:15.110
Saeed ibn Zaid radiallahu anhu

00:37:15.110 --> 00:37:17.410
his wife Fatima bint Al-Khattab

00:37:17.410 --> 00:37:19.610
she accepted Islam very early

00:37:19.610 --> 00:37:21.910
the sister of Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu

00:37:21.910 --> 00:37:23.910
she accepted Islam very early

00:37:23.910 --> 00:37:26.910
another one who accepted Islam was Khabbab ibn Al-Arat

00:37:26.910 --> 00:37:29.410
we will come to his story as well inshallah

00:37:29.410 --> 00:37:32.810
and Khalid ibn Saeed ibn Al-Aas

00:37:32.810 --> 00:37:36.610
and another one who accepted Islam from the Makhzum tribe

00:37:36.610 --> 00:37:39.610
was a man known as Al-Arqam

00:37:39.610 --> 00:37:41.210
ibn Abi Al-Arqam

00:37:41.210 --> 00:37:43.010
he was also in his teens

00:37:43.010 --> 00:37:46.010
and he accepted Islam from a very lofty family

00:37:46.010 --> 00:37:51.010
a lot of these people Quraish was scared of harming them

00:37:51.010 --> 00:37:53.910
because of the family, because of the clan

00:37:53.910 --> 00:37:55.710
sometimes people want to beat you up

00:37:55.710 --> 00:37:57.210
but they see you've got a brother

00:37:57.210 --> 00:37:58.610
so they look, they say

00:37:58.610 --> 00:38:00.210
you didn't have that guy as your brother

00:38:00.210 --> 00:38:01.910
we would have beaten him up Subhanallah

00:38:01.910 --> 00:38:03.910
or they see you've got a bit of power

00:38:03.910 --> 00:38:05.710
or you do business with them

00:38:05.710 --> 00:38:07.910
so they keep quiet because of the business

00:38:07.910 --> 00:38:10.410
this is the policy of the people of Quraish

00:38:10.410 --> 00:38:12.110
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:38:12.110 --> 00:38:14.610
grant us forgiveness and steadfastness

00:38:14.610 --> 00:38:17.010
so Al-Arqam ibn Abi Al-Arqam

00:38:17.010 --> 00:38:22.010
his house was then used as a secret meeting point

00:38:22.010 --> 00:38:24.410
to learn and study revelation

00:38:24.410 --> 00:38:26.410
and the deen that was being revealed

00:38:26.410 --> 00:38:28.510
the verses at the time that were being revealed

00:38:28.510 --> 00:38:31.010
were connected to the oneness of Allah

00:38:31.010 --> 00:38:32.510
subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:38:32.510 --> 00:38:34.310
belief in the life after death

00:38:34.310 --> 00:38:35.910
heaven and hell

00:38:36.010 --> 00:38:43.210
and the various teachings of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:38:43.210 --> 00:38:45.010
connected to belief

00:38:45.010 --> 00:38:47.310
because that was what was the most important thing

00:38:47.310 --> 00:38:48.610
at that particular time

00:38:48.610 --> 00:38:50.610
the belief had to be corrected

00:38:50.610 --> 00:38:52.610
it was filthy at the time

00:38:52.610 --> 00:38:56.010
and it would only be cleansed through tawheed

00:38:56.010 --> 00:38:59.310
and this is why one of the most important aspects

00:38:59.310 --> 00:39:01.110
was the fact that these idols

00:39:01.110 --> 00:39:04.910
and everything besides Allah

00:39:04.910 --> 00:39:06.310
cannot harm or benefit

00:39:06.310 --> 00:39:09.810
it is only Allah who is in absolute control of everything

00:39:09.810 --> 00:39:12.510
so you worship Allah alone

00:39:12.510 --> 00:39:15.210
so they used to gather in the house of Al-Arqam ibn Abi Al-Arqam

00:39:15.210 --> 00:39:16.410
radiallahu anhu

00:39:16.410 --> 00:39:18.710
and they used to learn the verses

00:39:18.710 --> 00:39:20.610
that were being revealed one by one

00:39:20.610 --> 00:39:23.810
remember the verses were not all revealed at once

00:39:23.810 --> 00:39:25.910
but they were revealed bit by bit

00:39:25.910 --> 00:39:28.510
as something happened the verses were revealed inshallah

00:39:28.510 --> 00:39:32.110
we will get to see a little bit more of that later on in the month

00:39:32.110 --> 00:39:34.610
then we have subhanallah

00:39:34.610 --> 00:39:37.410
something very important

00:39:37.410 --> 00:39:38.610
what happened is

00:39:38.610 --> 00:39:40.510
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:39:40.510 --> 00:39:43.110
met Jibreel alayhi sallatu wa sallam once

00:39:43.110 --> 00:39:45.310
when he was in a certain part of Mecca

00:39:45.310 --> 00:39:47.710
and Jibreel alayhi sallatu wa sallam

00:39:47.710 --> 00:39:49.310
taught him wudhu

00:39:49.310 --> 00:39:50.810
wudhu is the ablution

00:39:50.810 --> 00:39:55.210
how we wash ourselves before we come in for prayer and salah

00:39:55.210 --> 00:39:56.810
and how that happened is

00:39:56.810 --> 00:39:58.810
a little rock was made

00:39:58.810 --> 00:40:01.110
to gush water from

00:40:01.110 --> 00:40:04.410
and that water was used for Jibreel alayhi sallam

00:40:04.410 --> 00:40:06.410
who had come in the form of a human being

00:40:06.410 --> 00:40:08.910
to make wudhu whilst Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:40:08.910 --> 00:40:12.210
was watching and then he repeated the wudhu

00:40:12.210 --> 00:40:14.610
and then Jibreel alayhi sallam

00:40:14.610 --> 00:40:16.610
taught him salah

00:40:16.610 --> 00:40:19.410
and Ibn Hisham makes mention of this in his seerah

00:40:19.410 --> 00:40:21.910
that Jibreel alayhi sallam

00:40:21.910 --> 00:40:24.010
taught Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:40:24.010 --> 00:40:26.710
salah at the very early stages

00:40:26.710 --> 00:40:30.510
although it was not compulsory as it is today

00:40:30.510 --> 00:40:32.310
when salah was first revealed

00:40:32.310 --> 00:40:35.210
it was only two rak'ah at a time

00:40:35.210 --> 00:40:37.410
mathna mathna two rak'ah two rak'ah

00:40:37.410 --> 00:40:40.510
and it was a means of ibadah

00:40:40.510 --> 00:40:41.710
an act of worship

00:40:41.710 --> 00:40:43.110
those who wanted to worship

00:40:43.110 --> 00:40:45.810
this is the way they would worship Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:40:45.810 --> 00:40:48.410
put their heads on the ground for Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:40:48.410 --> 00:40:50.710
slightly different from what came later on

00:40:50.710 --> 00:40:54.210
we know that salah became compulsory at mi'raj

00:40:54.210 --> 00:40:56.210
but it was taught before that

00:40:56.210 --> 00:40:57.910
because Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:40:57.910 --> 00:40:59.510
used to read salah at night

00:40:59.510 --> 00:41:00.910
and the sahabah radiallahu anhum

00:41:00.910 --> 00:41:02.110
prior to mi'raj

00:41:02.110 --> 00:41:04.510
they used to offer voluntary prayers at night

00:41:04.510 --> 00:41:06.810
this is mentioned in the surahs in the Quran

00:41:06.810 --> 00:41:08.110
and this is how it had started

00:41:08.110 --> 00:41:09.510
so if someone asks you

00:41:09.510 --> 00:41:11.710
when was salah made compulsory

00:41:11.710 --> 00:41:13.510
you say upon mi'raj

00:41:13.510 --> 00:41:17.310
and when was salah taught to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:41:17.310 --> 00:41:19.210
in the early stages

00:41:19.210 --> 00:41:21.210
during the silent call

00:41:21.210 --> 00:41:25.010
to the family members and friends

00:41:25.010 --> 00:41:26.310
in Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:41:26.310 --> 00:41:27.810
we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:41:27.810 --> 00:41:29.510
to make us steadfast with salah

00:41:29.510 --> 00:41:31.910
we look at salah today as a burden

00:41:31.910 --> 00:41:36.910
yet it was given as a gift by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to us

00:41:36.910 --> 00:41:39.310
the day we consider salah a gift

00:41:39.310 --> 00:41:42.910
we will be able to achieve its true sweetness

00:41:42.910 --> 00:41:45.910
and we will be able to taste the benefit of that salah

00:41:45.910 --> 00:41:49.510
when we fulfill salah because we want to fulfill it

00:41:49.510 --> 00:41:51.510
not because we have to fulfill it

00:41:51.510 --> 00:41:54.210
as I said earlier before the Isha salah

00:41:54.210 --> 00:41:56.410
there is a difference between fulfilling a prayer

00:41:56.410 --> 00:41:58.110
because you have to do it

00:41:58.110 --> 00:42:00.210
and doing it because you want to do it

00:42:00.210 --> 00:42:04.010
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us from those who fulfill it

00:42:04.010 --> 00:42:05.710
because we want to fulfill it

00:42:05.710 --> 00:42:08.010
and may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala accept it from us

00:42:08.010 --> 00:42:10.910
so that was a little bit about the history of how

00:42:10.910 --> 00:42:15.110
salah was taught to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:42:15.110 --> 00:42:17.810
then we have another very very interesting incident

00:42:17.810 --> 00:42:20.410
that occurred at the time of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:42:20.410 --> 00:42:22.610
at that stage when they wanted to pray

00:42:22.610 --> 00:42:24.210
they used to go out, they used to hide

00:42:24.210 --> 00:42:26.010
they used to go into some of the valleys

00:42:26.010 --> 00:42:28.410
they used to go to the outlying areas of Makkah

00:42:28.410 --> 00:42:29.810
and they used to pray

00:42:29.810 --> 00:42:33.410
and they had not yet got to 40 people

00:42:33.410 --> 00:42:34.810
30 something people

00:42:34.810 --> 00:42:37.710
that is the number of people who had accepted

00:42:37.710 --> 00:42:39.510
slowly but surely

00:42:39.510 --> 00:42:41.610
and then Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:42:41.610 --> 00:42:45.410
revealed verses to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:42:45.410 --> 00:42:51.810
وَأَنذِرْ عَشِيرَتَكَ الْأَقْرَبِينَ

00:42:51.810 --> 00:42:56.610
warn your family, your tribesmen, the kindred, those around you

00:42:56.610 --> 00:42:59.010
warn them

00:42:59.010 --> 00:43:01.510
now that meant that now we can no longer be silent

00:43:01.510 --> 00:43:03.310
we now got to warn the people

00:43:03.310 --> 00:43:06.310
so what did Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam do?

00:43:06.310 --> 00:43:08.310
I'm going to make mention of the story

00:43:08.310 --> 00:43:11.310
which is very moving and very touching

00:43:11.310 --> 00:43:15.810
and it should serve as a lesson to all of us

00:43:15.810 --> 00:43:18.510
he gathered the people of the tribes

00:43:18.510 --> 00:43:21.010
that were considered his own asheera

00:43:21.010 --> 00:43:23.710
his own people

00:43:23.710 --> 00:43:26.810
he called them tribe by tribe

00:43:26.810 --> 00:43:29.910
from the mount of Safa where he had climbed up

00:43:29.910 --> 00:43:31.610
it was quite a high mount

00:43:31.610 --> 00:43:36.310
he climbed up and he began to call the names of these little tribes

00:43:36.310 --> 00:43:39.310
and he called the names of certain people as well

00:43:39.310 --> 00:43:41.010
so everyone was shocked

00:43:41.010 --> 00:43:42.310
because there was rumour around

00:43:42.310 --> 00:43:45.310
and there was persecution obviously, individually

00:43:45.310 --> 00:43:47.110
but on a wholesale level

00:43:47.110 --> 00:43:49.510
no one dared had the guts

00:43:49.510 --> 00:43:53.210
to do what Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam had just done

00:43:53.210 --> 00:43:54.710
and this is why they were shocked

00:43:54.810 --> 00:43:57.010
this man has just called out

00:43:57.010 --> 00:43:59.810
what is it? is he wanting to give up everything?

00:43:59.810 --> 00:44:02.410
well if that happens then it will be good for us

00:44:02.410 --> 00:44:05.410
but they were in for something else

00:44:05.410 --> 00:44:08.610
as they went some of the leaders couldn't make it

00:44:08.610 --> 00:44:10.210
so they sent representatives

00:44:10.210 --> 00:44:12.510
one of the people who came there Abu Lahab

00:44:12.510 --> 00:44:16.010
who was one of the uncles of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:44:16.010 --> 00:44:20.110
he was actually an uncle of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:44:20.110 --> 00:44:22.210
and he arrived there

00:44:22.210 --> 00:44:24.310
and they all looking and listening and waiting

00:44:24.310 --> 00:44:26.010
what is this man about to say?

00:44:26.010 --> 00:44:27.210
so he makes an announcement

00:44:27.210 --> 00:44:29.810
and he's standing at the top and they all listening to him

00:44:29.810 --> 00:44:32.510
he says if I were to tell you

00:44:32.510 --> 00:44:34.910
that at the back of this mountain

00:44:34.910 --> 00:44:37.410
there is an army of horsemen

00:44:37.410 --> 00:44:40.110
coming to attack you, to destroy you

00:44:40.110 --> 00:44:43.110
would you believe what I have just said?

00:44:43.110 --> 00:44:44.110
and all of them said

00:44:44.110 --> 00:44:47.710
yes indeed we have never heard you lie

00:44:47.710 --> 00:44:48.810
imagine

00:44:48.810 --> 00:44:52.110
we have never heard you lie

00:44:52.110 --> 00:44:54.410
subhanallah

00:44:54.410 --> 00:44:56.610
we would believe you immediately

00:44:56.610 --> 00:44:57.610
he says

00:44:57.610 --> 00:45:03.410
فَإِنِّ نَذِيرٌ لَكُمْ بَيْنَ يَدَي عَذَابٍ شَدِيدٍ

00:45:03.410 --> 00:45:05.510
so I am warning you

00:45:05.510 --> 00:45:08.810
of a severe punishment that is about to come

00:45:08.810 --> 00:45:09.510
subhanallah

00:45:09.510 --> 00:45:13.210
I am warning you of a punishment that is about to come

00:45:13.210 --> 00:45:15.110
and then he began to tell them

00:45:15.110 --> 00:45:17.610
to do good deeds because

00:45:17.610 --> 00:45:20.810
he will not be able to save them from that fire

00:45:20.910 --> 00:45:25.010
or from that punishment just because he is a tribesman

00:45:25.010 --> 00:45:26.710
or he is a family man

00:45:26.710 --> 00:45:28.010
or he is a relative

00:45:28.010 --> 00:45:29.810
he won't be able to save them

00:45:29.810 --> 00:45:31.010
so he came out

00:45:31.010 --> 00:45:32.610
saying the names of the clans

00:45:32.610 --> 00:45:33.310
he says

00:45:33.310 --> 00:45:35.210
save yourself from the fire

00:45:35.210 --> 00:45:37.010
saying the names of certain people

00:45:37.010 --> 00:45:38.710
save yourself from the fire

00:45:38.710 --> 00:45:40.610
for I will not be able to help you

00:45:40.610 --> 00:45:42.810
and he delivered the message openly

00:45:42.810 --> 00:45:46.710
so that was the reason why he had gathered them

00:45:46.710 --> 00:45:48.910
around that Mount Safa

00:45:48.910 --> 00:45:51.210
and how he started the message

00:45:51.210 --> 00:45:55.110
just to prove to them that you consider me truthful

00:45:55.110 --> 00:45:57.810
if I were to lie

00:45:57.810 --> 00:46:01.310
I would not have lied about this particular thing

00:46:01.310 --> 00:46:03.210
and you know that I am not a liar

00:46:03.210 --> 00:46:05.110
but still Abu Lahab

00:46:05.110 --> 00:46:07.010
with his big mouth

00:46:07.010 --> 00:46:10.410
and arrogance because of his standing in Quraysh

00:46:10.410 --> 00:46:13.610
and he was the son of a top leader of Quraysh

00:46:13.610 --> 00:46:14.910
and this was his nephew

00:46:14.910 --> 00:46:17.210
but he had no respect for his nephew

00:46:17.210 --> 00:46:22.510
because this would mean he's acknowledging a man above him

00:46:22.510 --> 00:46:24.110
you see this was the problem with the people

00:46:24.110 --> 00:46:25.210
they did not want to accept

00:46:25.210 --> 00:46:29.210
because they would be acknowledging someone above them

00:46:29.210 --> 00:46:31.410
they thought we're going to lose our power

00:46:31.410 --> 00:46:34.810
we're going to lose this throne that we're sitting on

00:46:34.810 --> 00:46:36.010
the wealth that we're sitting on

00:46:36.010 --> 00:46:38.310
this man is going to take over everything

00:46:38.310 --> 00:46:40.110
and if we acknowledge and we accept

00:46:40.110 --> 00:46:41.510
what will happen to us

00:46:41.510 --> 00:46:42.710
so they refused

00:46:42.710 --> 00:46:43.710
Abu Lahab says

00:46:43.710 --> 00:46:46.010
تَبَّلَّكَ يَا مُحَمَّدُ

00:46:46.010 --> 00:46:48.810
destruction be upon you O Muhammad

00:46:48.810 --> 00:46:50.610
أَلِي هَذَا جَمَعْتَنَا

00:46:50.610 --> 00:46:53.710
is this why you gathered us here

00:46:53.710 --> 00:46:55.010
and the people were looking at him

00:46:55.010 --> 00:46:56.310
because he had the guts

00:46:56.310 --> 00:46:58.110
that was a swear word basically

00:46:58.110 --> 00:47:01.010
meaning insulting Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:47:01.010 --> 00:47:02.010
تَبَّلَّكَ

00:47:02.010 --> 00:47:04.310
the others were quiet

00:47:04.310 --> 00:47:06.210
so what happened

00:47:06.210 --> 00:47:09.210
Allah سبحانه وتعالى sent

00:47:09.210 --> 00:47:12.410
Jibreel عليه الصلاة والسلام

00:47:12.410 --> 00:47:14.110
with one of the most powerful

00:47:14.110 --> 00:47:16.110
most eloquent surahs

00:47:16.110 --> 00:47:19.210
that had been revealed up to that time

00:47:19.210 --> 00:47:23.610
and so easy to memorize

00:47:23.610 --> 00:47:25.510
that even the children of Quraysh

00:47:25.510 --> 00:47:27.010
memorize these verses

00:47:27.010 --> 00:47:28.810
and on the streets

00:47:28.810 --> 00:47:30.410
everyone was uttering them

00:47:30.410 --> 00:47:32.510
Muslim and non-Muslim

00:47:32.510 --> 00:47:33.310
Subhanallah

